    <string name="settings_supply_title">Supply inference</string>
    <string name="settings_supply_on">Charging-first beta active. Teale supplies while the phone is charging and cool enough.</string>
    <string name="settings_supply_off">When on, this phone joins the Teale WAN as a small-model beta supply node.</string>
    <string name="settings_supply_beta_title">Android supply beta</string>
    <string name="settings_supply_beta_body">Phones are best-effort supply nodes. Teale pauses when the phone is unplugged or too hot and is tuned for small-model overflow capacity, not always-on backbone throughput.</string>
    <string name="settings_supply_charging_only_title">Only supply while charging</string>
    <string name="settings_supply_charging_only_body">Recommended. Android is much more reliable for supply when the phone is docked or on AC power.</string>
    <string name="settings_supply_acceleration_title">Acceleration mode</string>
    <string name="settings_supply_acceleration_auto">Auto (accelerated beta)</string>
    <string name="settings_supply_acceleration_auto_body">Try the Vulkan-backed profile on capable phones, then fall back to CPU if startup fails.</string>
    <string name="settings_supply_acceleration_cpu">CPU only (conservative)</string>
    <string name="settings_supply_acceleration_cpu_body">Use the small, conservative CPU profile for lower-risk bring-up and overnight stability testing.</string>
    <string name="settings_invite">Invite friend via SMS</string>
    <string name="settings_scale_title">Distributed inference at scale</string>
    <string name="settings_scale_body">Teale scales through request-level parallelism: each online phone runs a full small model (Gemma 3 1B, Qwen 2.5 1.5B). The gateway routes each incoming request to one phone. Thousands of phones = thousands of parallel inferences. Phone-mesh sharding for bigger models will land on LAN-local peers (same Wi-Fi) first.</string>
